      1. Third of men in the UK thought that if a woman had flirted on a date, it wouldnt be considered rape if she hadnt explicitly consented to sex.
      2. One in 10 people werent even sure or didnt think it was rape to have sex with a woman who was very drunk or asleep.
      3. A third of people in the UK think it isnt usually rape if a woman is pressured into having sex but there is no physical violence
      4. A quarter believed sex without consent in long-term relationships was usu...ally not rape

      A survey commissioned by the End Violence Against Women Coalition.
